  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "Facebook does not provide a way to see who specifically views your profile or posts. The platform prioritizes user privacy and does not offer tools to track profile visitors. Here are a few points related to this topic:\n\n1. **Privacy Settings**: You can adjust your privacy settings to control who can see your posts, but this won't give you information about who has viewed your profile.\n\n2. **Third-Party Apps**: Be wary of any third-party applications claiming to show you profile viewers. These are often scams or violate Facebook's terms of service and can compromise your account security.\n\n3. **Post Interactions**: While you can't see who views your profile, you can see who interacts with your content, such as likes, comments, and shares.\n\n4. **Story Views**: If you post stories on Facebook, you can see who has viewed them since stories are designed to have a more ephemeral and interactive experience.\n\nIf your goal is to engage with your audience, focus on creating quality content and fostering conversation rather than tracking who views your profile.",
